We meet on the side walk next to the softball field along 55th street. 

This park is big and different Qs pick different places to workout, if you are late it is possible you won’t be able to find the PAX. Be there on time or early. 6:25 PM is the recommend arrival time.

Parking can be hit or miss depending on what other activities are going on at the park that evening so plan to get there at least 5 minutes early in case you need to park a couple blocks away. If you need to park away from the site, try to park by Ravenna Brewing so your walk after beers is short!

Traffic is also hit or miss so take that into account.

This AO is meant to be inviting to FNGs who might be of the opinion that F3 starts too early. Invite folks and we try to align Qs to be workable for everyone.

Can you pronounce Bolm-Schuhkraft Park? Well, it’s also know as City Park and is a sprawling 44.5 acres park located at 1200 Evergreen Lane in Columbia, IL. We in F3 call it “The Black Forest”. It’s a perfect place for your morning workout!

The Black Forest is well stocked for an F3 mother-of-all beatdowns. It’s got benches and picnic tables, 4 pavilions with tables (really useful on those wet, dreary mornings), basketball courts, batting cages, exercise stations, horseshoe pits, a 1 mile paved trail, roller hockey rink, sand volleyball court, sports fields, tennis courts, and more! Gosh I’m exhausted just rattling that off. Workout Q’s can get really creative here!
